      "text": [
        " إِدْمَانُ الْخُفِّ يَقِي مِيتَةَ السَّوْءِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Muhammad Bin Abdullah, from Ali Al Baghdady, from Abu Al Hassan Al Zareyr, from Abu Salma Al Sarraj, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Habitually wearing the sock prevents the evil death’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "6. A number of our people have narrated from Sahl ibn Ziyad from Muhammad ibn ‘Abd Allah from Ali al-Baghdadiy from abu al- Hassan al-Darir from abu Salmah al-Sarraj who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Continuously wearing al-Khuff (half-boot) is protection against dying badly.’” "
        ]
      }
